1:36:51.680 --> 1:36:54.141
- Do you really think this is legit?

1:36:54.141 --> 1:36:55.351
I mean, there's no way that Tom

1:36:55.351 --> 1:36:57.311
finished the research on his own.

1:36:57.311 --> 1:36:58.729
Hey, no wasting, right?

1:36:59.605 --> 1:37:02.399
- Look at the code
samples on the algorithm.

1:37:02.399 --> 1:37:04.401
This is definitely new
work. No doubt about it.

1:37:04.401 --> 1:37:06.654
- Okay, but we took all the
important research materials

1:37:06.654 --> 1:37:08.155
from the lab.

1:37:08.155 --> 1:37:10.866
- That may be true, but the
goose that laid the golden egg

1:37:10.866 --> 1:37:13.285
just landed in our lap for a second time.

1:37:15.579 --> 1:37:19.208
- I'm not sure that I follow.

1:37:22.336 --> 1:37:26.382
- Okay, listen, Darjeeling
Limited, emphasis on the limited,

1:37:26.382 --> 1:37:28.217
we will test the Mint.

1:37:28.217 --> 1:37:30.886
- If it works, like he says it should,

1:37:30.886 --> 1:37:33.556
we will take it from him.

1:37:33.556 --> 1:37:35.850
- He's not just gonna hand
it over to you, is he?

1:37:35.850 --> 1:37:37.309
No Bruno, he's not.

1:37:41.605 --> 1:37:43.399
- No. No, no, no, no, no.

1:37:43.399 --> 1:37:44.400
Okay, you're not expecting me

1:37:44.400 --> 1:37:46.360
to surrogate load Tom again, are you?

1:37:46.360 --> 1:37:47.528
- Exactly.

1:37:47.528 --> 1:37:49.864
- I'm sorry, but that's
not gonna happen, okay?

1:37:49.864 --> 1:37:52.157
Ever since you loaded
that dog brain onto me,

1:37:52.157 --> 1:37:54.076
I've been dreaming in muted colors, okay?

1:37:54.076 --> 1:37:55.327
So, I'm sorry, but no.

1:37:57.580 --> 1:38:00.499
- What if I doubled what
I gave you last time?

1:38:01.876 --> 1:38:02.710
- No.

1:38:04.837 --> 1:38:06.380
- Okay.

1:38:06.380 --> 1:38:07.673
How about if I tripled it?

1:38:11.594 --> 1:38:15.639
A hundred and fifty grand
buys a few nice rice rockets.

1:38:17.016 --> 1:38:18.559
It's a no brainer, Speed Racer.

1:38:25.316 --> 1:38:26.901
- Okay, sure.

1:38:37.202 --> 1:38:39.204
- Oh, mornin', hon.

1:38:39.204 --> 1:38:40.039
- Morning.

1:38:41.707 --> 1:38:43.542
How'd you sleep, Mr. Kirk?

1:38:43.542 --> 1:38:45.210
- Tossed and turned all night.

1:38:45.210 --> 1:38:46.545
What about you?

1:38:46.545 --> 1:38:47.379
- Yeah, me too.

1:38:48.672 --> 1:38:49.924
Feelin' a little jittery.

1:38:51.091 --> 1:38:52.426
We'll be all right.

1:38:57.139 --> 1:38:57.973
- Tom?

1:38:58.974 --> 1:38:59.808
- Yep.

1:39:03.938 --> 1:39:04.772
You okay?

1:39:11.236 --> 1:39:16.116
Thank you for everything
you've done for me and my dad.

1:39:17.201 --> 1:39:19.078
I mean, if everything goes, well, if,

1:39:21.580 --> 1:39:23.248
maybe we can do that second date.

1:39:25.960 --> 1:39:26.794
Ya know?

1:39:35.511 --> 1:39:36.637
Hey, Bruno, what's up?

1:39:36.637 --> 1:39:38.097
Hey, Tom, how are you?

1:39:38.097 --> 1:39:39.473
- I'm good.

1:39:39.473 --> 1:39:40.933
You talk to Rocky yet?

1:39:40.933 --> 1:39:42.476
Listen, could
you meet me at the bar

1:39:42.476 --> 1:39:44.311
in about 10 minutes?

1:39:44.311 --> 1:39:45.813
Got something important to discuss.

1:39:45.813 --> 1:39:47.856
- Right now? No, man, I can't.

1:39:47.856 --> 1:39:51.235
It's about Rocky.
I'll see ya there in 10.

1:39:51.235 --> 1:39:53.237
- What was that about?

1:39:53.237 --> 1:39:55.656
- That was Bruno. He wants
me to meet him at the bar.

1:39:56.573 --> 1:39:57.408
- I'm coming.

1:40:26.478 --> 1:40:28.814
- Hey, Tom. How's it goin'?

1:40:28.814 --> 1:40:29.648
- Good.

1:40:29.648 --> 1:40:31.525
- So, I heard you made some
progress on the research.

1:40:31.525 --> 1:40:32.359
- I did.

1:40:34.862 --> 1:40:37.865
- Well, first off, I
really wanna thank you.

1:40:44.997 --> 1:40:46.540
- Yo, what are you?

1:40:46.540 --> 1:40:47.374
- I'm really sorry about this.

1:40:47.374 --> 1:40:49.251
- Bruno, stop!

1:40:49.251 --> 1:40:52.129
- I tried showing you
the good side of life.

1:40:52.129 --> 1:40:54.715
Then you went all Dalai Lama on me.

1:40:54.715 --> 1:40:56.300
- Come on!

1:41:00.596 --> 1:41:05.434
I mean, really, man, how do
you say no to a '66 Vette, huh?

1:41:05.434 --> 1:41:07.644
- You just think you're so...

1:41:07.644 --> 1:41:09.104
Think you're so...

1:41:42.096 --> 1:41:42.930
- Tom!

1:41:44.473 --> 1:41:46.391
Hey, are you okay?

1:41:47.768 --> 1:41:48.894
Tom!

1:41:48.894 --> 1:41:49.728
- That's you.

1:41:51.188 --> 1:41:52.564
Tell her you're almost done!

1:41:54.650 --> 1:41:55.567
- I'm almost done.

1:42:05.077 --> 1:42:05.911
- Okay, okay.

1:42:05.911 --> 1:42:09.206
So, I go back to the farm, I get the Mint,

1:42:09.206 --> 1:42:10.499
and I bring it back to you.

1:42:10.499 --> 1:42:11.333
- That's right.

1:42:11.333 --> 1:42:14.586
And to me and to no one else, okay?

1:42:14.586 --> 1:42:15.671
- Okay, I got it.

1:42:15.671 --> 1:42:17.923
- Okay, now get out of
here before TICS sets it.

1:42:17.923 --> 1:42:18.715
- How?

1:42:18.715 --> 1:42:19.800
- Just check your pockets.

1:42:24.721 --> 1:42:25.597
- Nice.

1:42:34.648 --> 1:42:36.316
- Hey! Tom, hey!

1:42:36.316 --> 1:42:41.321
Where are you going?

1:42:48.871 --> 1:42:51.039
Pick up, pick up, pick up.

1:43:04.553 --> 1:43:06.138
Rocky, this is Bruno.

1:43:06.138 --> 1:43:08.599
I asked Tom to meet me
at the Rusty Tavern.

1:43:08.599 --> 1:43:10.726
I'm waiting outside. Meet me here.

1:43:16.607 --> 1:43:18.275
- Did you call Tom?

1:43:18.275 --> 1:43:19.109
- Yeah.

1:43:20.235 --> 1:43:21.486
When is he coming?

1:43:21.486 --> 1:43:24.364
- He already did. I surrogate loaded him.

1:43:24.364 --> 1:43:27.451
- Really? Nicely done Potter boy.

1:43:29.620 --> 1:43:31.121
- 150Ks isn't gonna cut it.

1:43:32.331 --> 1:43:33.624
I want at least 2 million.

1:43:35.375 --> 1:43:36.210
- Excuse me?

1:43:37.586 --> 1:43:39.087
- You and I both know that a hold time

1:43:39.087 --> 1:43:41.715
that's over 18 hours is worth millions.

1:43:43.675 --> 1:43:44.509
- I see.

1:43:47.304 --> 1:43:48.805
And if I don't pay?

1:43:49.932 --> 1:43:51.391
I'll call the sheik.

1:43:53.227 --> 1:43:54.978
- You think you're smart, huh?

1:43:54.978 --> 1:43:56.563
A real brainiac?

1:43:56.563 --> 1:43:58.440
- I'd like to think so, yeah.

1:43:58.440 --> 1:44:01.360
- Do you know the inferior brain paradox?

1:44:03.904 --> 1:44:06.406
The less it knows, the
more it thinks it knows.

1:44:18.252 --> 1:44:20.754
- My surrogate's never
gonna give you that device.

1:44:21.838 --> 1:44:23.465
- That may be.

1:44:23.465 --> 1:44:24.675
So put your hands there.

1:44:28.971 --> 1:44:31.473
Now, this is what we will use.

1:44:40.357 --> 1:44:41.733
- You selfish pig.

1:44:41.733 --> 1:44:45.028
- Maybe, but you know what
happens with selfless pigs?

1:46:18.914 --> 1:46:19.748
- Howdy.

1:46:30.801 --> 1:46:33.804
Can I get ya anything? A beer maybe?

1:46:38.475 --> 1:46:40.519
What kinda beer is that?

1:46:40.519 --> 1:46:42.354
- It's not a beer, my
,

1:46:42.354 --> 1:46:43.522
it's you.

1:46:43.522 --> 1:46:45.357
You're beautiful.

1:46:45.357 --> 1:46:48.777
Thank you.

1:46:52.155 --> 1:46:54.032
You know, we're inside, right?

1:46:57.285 --> 1:46:59.037
- Thank you.

1:46:59.037 --> 1:47:03.917
- Wow, you have beautiful eyes.

1:47:04.793 --> 1:47:05.877
- I've been told.

1:47:05.877 --> 1:47:07.421
- You have?

1:47:07.421 --> 1:47:08.713
Why am I not surprised.

1:47:10.715 --> 1:47:14.136
Wow, I could just stare into them all day.

1:47:16.888 --> 1:47:18.640
Oh, I'm up here.

1:47:34.990 --> 1:47:36.032
You feelin' okay?

1:47:37.492 --> 1:47:38.326
- You.

1:47:39.327 --> 1:47:42.873
- And you thought you could
get away with killing my Kirk.

1:47:42.873 --> 1:47:43.707
- You.

1:47:47.544 --> 1:47:48.378
- Adios.

1:48:10.484 --> 1:48:11.985
- Okay, where'd you say he is?

1:48:13.153 --> 1:48:14.279
- Outside in his car.

1:48:16.823 --> 1:48:18.116
- Quick, gimme your phone.

1:48:19.284 --> 1:48:20.118
Come on, gimme your phone.

1:48:20.118 --> 1:48:20.952
- Okay.

1:48:26.208 --> 1:48:27.667
- What? We're out of options.

1:48:27.667 --> 1:48:28.793
This is all we've got.

1:48:30.253 --> 1:48:31.046
- I don't know.

1:48:32.464 --> 1:48:33.381
It's risky.

1:48:34.633 --> 1:48:35.634
Look, you don't have to do this.

1:48:35.634 --> 1:48:37.844
Oh, I do, for my dad.

1:48:43.350 --> 1:48:44.768
- I wanna ask you somethin'.

1:48:49.189 --> 1:48:50.941
- What happened to Kirk that night?

1:48:52.943 --> 1:48:54.611
- What's going on?

1:48:54.611 --> 1:48:56.613
Is this TICS setting in?

1:48:56.613 --> 1:48:57.405
- Just tell me.

1:48:58.990 --> 1:49:00.283
- Get back inside.

1:49:01.701 --> 1:49:02.619
- I need answers.

1:49:02.619 --> 1:49:03.745
- I'll go get the Mint.

1:49:03.745 --> 1:49:05.080
- Bruno.
- Just stay put.

1:49:05.956 --> 1:49:06.790
I'm not Bruno.

1:49:06.790 --> 1:49:08.667
- Bruno, wait. Bruno, wait!

1:49:11.628 --> 1:49:14.047
- Hey! Hey, what happened?

1:49:14.047 --> 1:49:15.674
- We gotta get to the farm now.

1:49:15.674 --> 1:49:16.550
- How?

1:49:16.550 --> 1:49:17.926
- Get in.
- Okay.

1:49:45.870 --> 1:49:47.789
911, state your emergency.

1:49:47.789 --> 1:49:49.791
- Hi, I'd like to report
a possible shooting

1:49:49.791 --> 1:49:51.751
at Blue Mountain Farms in Elgin.

1:49:52.711 --> 1:49:54.296
Sir, are you safe?

1:49:54.296 --> 1:49:55.505
- Yes.

1:49:55.505 --> 1:49:57.591
Do you need medical-

1:50:12.814 --> 1:50:14.190
- What are you doing here?

1:50:14.190 --> 1:50:15.650
Why aren't you at the bar?

1:50:15.650 --> 1:50:17.569
- I need to ask you something.

1:50:17.569 --> 1:50:19.863
- I don't have time
for this. Just go back.

1:50:19.863 --> 1:50:22.657
- Tell me this one thing and
I'll do whatever you want.

1:50:22.657 --> 1:50:24.034
You've got to be kidding me.

1:50:24.034 --> 1:50:26.286
- What did you to Kirk?

1:50:26.286 --> 1:50:28.496
- This is what you want to know right now?

1:50:28.496 --> 1:50:30.999
- What happened to Kirk that night?

1:50:30.999 --> 1:50:31.833
- Okay, okay.

1:50:33.752 --> 1:50:37.047
I asked Bruno to surrogate load
onto Tom to steal the Mint.

1:50:37.047 --> 1:50:39.633
He ran into Dr. Kirk,
panicked, and killed him.

1:50:44.137 --> 1:50:46.056
- You killed Dr. Kirk Davis?

1:50:46.056 --> 1:50:47.140
- No, no, not me.

1:50:47.140 --> 1:50:49.100
Bruno did.

1:50:59.861 --> 1:51:03.281
- What are you doing here? We had a deal.

1:51:05.909 --> 1:51:07.327
- Gimme the laptop and files.

1:51:08.662 --> 1:51:10.163
- No, no, no, give them to me.

1:51:15.001 --> 1:51:16.002
- Wait, who are you?

1:51:17.379 --> 1:51:19.714
- I don't have time to play who's who?

1:51:19.714 --> 1:51:22.884
Give me the laptop.
Goddamn it, we had a plan!

1:51:25.804 --> 1:51:28.473
- Okay, if I can't reason with you,

1:51:28.473 --> 1:51:30.225
then maybe you'll reason with this.

1:51:33.395 --> 1:51:36.856
Give me the laptop or
I'll blow your brains out.

1:51:58.128 --> 1:52:00.630
- Get back, step back. Step back!

1:52:03.550 --> 1:52:05.760
- Look, look, look, Rocky, I'm sorry.

1:52:05.760 --> 1:52:06.970
I shouldn't have asked for more money.

1:52:06.970 --> 1:52:09.806
We can just keep the original
deal and I'll walk away.

1:52:09.806 --> 1:52:13.643
- No, no more deals. Give me
the laptop and my body back.

1:52:15.645 --> 1:52:16.479
- Tom?

1:52:19.482 --> 1:52:22.610
I had nothing to do with this, okay.

1:52:22.610 --> 1:52:24.446
He killed your father.

1:52:24.446 --> 1:52:27.073
I promise if you let me go
you'll never see me again.

1:52:27.073 --> 1:52:27.866
I'll disappear.

1:52:30.994 --> 1:52:33.163
- You sleazy worm. Come here.

1:52:34.748 --> 1:52:36.750
- Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

1:52:36.750 --> 1:52:37.834
We can still get outta this.

1:52:37.834 --> 1:52:38.668
- How?

1:52:38.668 --> 1:52:41.212
- The phone. It's in my pocket.

1:52:41.212 --> 1:52:43.965
And the cops are on
their way. Do the math!

1:52:54.559 --> 1:52:56.811
We have him dead to rights.

1:52:57.687 --> 1:52:58.980
Know this, my boy.

1:52:58.980 --> 1:53:02.275
As you go, so goes your father's work.

1:53:02.275 --> 1:53:05.111
Mad lab assistant kills scientist father.

1:53:05.111 --> 1:53:07.447
Sentenced to life.

1:53:09.866 --> 1:53:13.787
Every second, of every
minute of every hour

1:53:13.787 --> 1:53:15.580
of every day your father devoted his life

1:53:15.580 --> 1:53:17.415
to memory transfer technology.

1:53:17.415 --> 1:53:22.295
It goes away with you.

1:53:22.295 --> 1:53:23.880
- Drop your weapon.

1:53:23.880 --> 1:53:24.714
Drop it now!

1:53:26.049 --> 1:53:26.925
Drop your weapon.

1:53:27.884 --> 1:53:30.386
That'll be your legacy.

1:53:30.386 --> 1:53:32.096
- Hey, I said I'll shoot.

1:53:32.096 --> 1:53:34.474
- Oh, you're smarter than that, Tom.

1:53:34.474 --> 1:53:35.433
You won't shoot yourself.

1:53:35.433 --> 1:53:37.811
- You're only as good as
the promises you make.

1:53:39.729 --> 1:53:42.273
And I promised my father
I'd continue his research.

1:53:43.483 --> 1:53:44.442
- Drop your weapon!

1:53:45.443 --> 1:53:46.236
- Shoot me.

1:53:48.154 --> 1:53:49.489
Kill yourself.

1:53:52.534 --> 1:53:55.495
Face it, you can't kill yourself, Tom.

1:53:59.040 --> 1:54:00.458
I can't shoot you, but...

1:54:05.463 --> 1:54:06.714
- Step away from the weapon.

1:54:06.714 --> 1:54:08.466
Drop it, step away, step away.

1:54:08.466 --> 1:54:10.051
Get down. Get down, get down, get down.

1:54:10.051 --> 1:54:12.262
- No, no, no, no, no. No.

1:54:12.262 --> 1:54:15.014
- Get down!

1:54:15.014 --> 1:54:17.517
- No, no, no, no, no.

1:54:17.517 --> 1:54:18.351
No! No!

1:54:19.769 --> 1:54:21.729
I got him, son, I got him.

1:54:21.729 --> 1:54:22.564
- No!

1:54:31.281 --> 1:54:32.740
An eye for an eye.

1:55:05.690 --> 1:55:07.191
Birthday, bud.

1:55:07.191 --> 1:55:08.026
- Bruno!

1:55:08.026 --> 1:55:08.902
- Bruno!

1:55:08.902 --> 1:55:10.111
- Sorry for everything.

1:55:10.111 --> 1:55:12.196
This is your
brain in digital form.

1:55:15.408 --> 1:55:16.534
Tom, are you okay?

1:55:16.534 --> 1:55:17.952
Dr. Davis.

1:55:17.952 --> 1:55:19.120
Tom.

1:57:01.931 --> 1:57:06.936
between father and son

1:57:07.145 --> 1:57:12.150
and the kingdom come

1:57:12.859 --> 1:57:17.864
till it makes me numb

1:57:33.379 --> 1:57:37.300
sure will be his last

1:57:48.561 --> 1:57:52.273
has now grown numb

1:58:28.643 --> 1:58:32.814
my fists clenched tight

1:58:39.904 --> 1:58:44.033
close to the borderline

1:59:02.343 --> 1:59:06.514
born and a time to die

1:59:17.400 --> 1:59:21.404
war and a time for peace

1:59:21.404 --> 1:59:25.032
and a time to speak

1:59:25.032 --> 1:59:28.870
gain and a time to lose

1:59:28.870 --> 1:59:32.456
and it's time to choose

1:59:36.127 --> 1:59:39.964
and a time to mourn

1:59:39.964 --> 1:59:43.843
and a time to build

1:59:51.434 --> 1:59:55.021
when he's been outgunned
